## Commands

**Frontend (run from theme root):**
```bash
npm run dev      # Vite dev server with HMR
npm run build    # Production build → public/build/
```

**PHP code style (Laravel Pint, via Composer):**
```bash
./vendor/bin/pint          # Fix all PHP files
./vendor/bin/pint --test   # Check only (no writes)
```

**Translations:**
```bash
npm run translate          # Generate .pot and update .po files
npm run translate:compile  # Compile .mo and .js translation files
```

## Architecture

### Request → View flow

1. WordPress resolves the template (e.g. `single.php`) → Sage maps it to a Blade view in `resources/views/`
2. Acorn boots the Laravel container; View Composers in `app/View/Composers/` inject data into views
3. `App` composer (`app/View/Composers/App.php`) runs on **every** view (`'*'`) and injects `$siteName`
4. The main layout `resources/views/layouts/app.blade.php` wraps all pages; sections `header` and `footer` come from `resources/views/sections/`

